<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.229.105162.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Atriplex pseudotatarica. A an overview of the plant B a twig with the inflorescence C a vegetative shoot D a shoot at fruiting. Origin of the material A Haryana, near Asan Khurd village, Nov 2022 B Haryana, near Asan Kalan village, Nov 2022 C Haryana, near Asan Kalan village, Aug 2022 D Haryana, near Panipat town, Oct 2014. Photographer: A, B A. Sukhorukov, C, D N. Singh." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/884978" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.229.105162.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Bract-like cover (A, B) and seeds (C, D) of A. pseudotatarica A cover of a female flower located below the main inflorescence B cover of a female flower located in the main inflorescence C black seed D yellowish-brown seed. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/884979" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.229.105162.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Records of A. pseudotatarica." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/884980" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.229.105162.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Maximum clade credibility tree from the BEAST analysis of the ITS + ETS Atriplex dataset. Bayesian posterior probabilities are given above the branches, bootstrap percentages of the maximum likelihood analyses are given below the branches." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/884981" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

